'''Dropbox'''
----
Below are instructions I followed to set up Dropbox on my system.

''Installation''
----
{{Emerge|{{Package|net-misc/dropbox}}}}

''Configuration''
----
Set the DROPBOX_USERS variable to the value of your regular $USER in ''/etc/conf.d/dropbox''.

Below is an example showing how to do so using the text editor ''ed(1)'':
{{Code||<pre>
root# DBOXUSER=your_regular_user_ID
root# ed /etc/conf.d/dropbox <<q
/DROPBOX_USERS/ s/".*"/"$DBOXUSER"/p
w
q
</pre>}}
Next, add the dropbox init script to the default runlevel:
{{RootCmd|rc-update add dropbox default}}
And start it:
{{RootCmd|cd /etc/init.d && ./dropbox start}}
Now, as a regular user run the command line shown below, which will create these directories in your $HOME directory:

<tt>
Dropbox/
.dropbox-dist/
.dropbox/
</tt>
{{Cmd|dropbox start}}
